TY  - JOUR
T1  - Decision Analysis by Augmented Probability Simulation
AU  - Bielza, Concha
AU  - Müller, Peter
AU  - Insua, David Ríos
Y1  - 1999/07/01
PY  - 1999
DA  - 1999/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.45.7.995
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.45.7.995
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 995
EP  - 1007
VL  - 45
IS  - 7
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - We provide a generic Monte Carlo method to find the alternative of maximum expected utility in a decision analysis. We define an artificial distribution on the product space of alternatives and states, and show that the optimal alternative is the mode of the implied marginal distribution on the alternatives. After drawing a sample from the artificial distribution, we may use exploratory data analysis tools to approximately identify the optimal alternative. We illustrate our method for some important types of influence diagrams.
AB  - We provide a generic Monte Carlo method to find the alternative of maximum expected utility in a decision analysis. We define an artificial distribution on the product space of alternatives and states, and show that the optimal alternative is the mode of the implied marginal distribution on the alternatives. After drawing a sample from the artificial distribution, we may use exploratory data analysis tools to approximately identify the optimal alternative. We illustrate our method for some important types of influence diagrams.
